# Case study reveal timer

Case studies with a pre-launch blur gate use a **worldwide UTC schedule**, not per-user `localStorage`.

## Source of truth

`src/lib/case-study-reveal-schedule.ts`

| Field | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| `startsAtUtc` | UTC ISO-8601 instant when the countdown starts (same for every visitor) |
| `CASE_STUDY_REVEAL_DURATION_MS` | Unlock window length — **20 hours** |

Unlock instant: `Date.parse(startsAtUtc) + 20 hours`

## Resetting the timer

1. Set `startsAtUtc` to the new UTC start (e.g. `2026-06-16T22:00:00.000Z`).
2. Do **not** bump storage keys or use `localStorage` for deadlines.
3. All users worldwide see the same remaining time.

## Wiring

- Hook: `useCaseStudyRevealCountdownForSlug(slug)` or `useCaseStudyRevealCountdown(unlockAtMs)`
- UI: `<CaseStudyRevealCountdown slug="cisco-policy-copilot" />`
- Blur gate: `isRevealed` from the same hook / slug schedule

## Do not

- Per-browser countdown (`Date.now() + duration` in `localStorage`)
- Different unlock times per user or timezone offset hacks — always UTC
